task 2

migrations = migrations %>% rename('target'='Current residence in...1') %>% 
  select(-contains('Current residence in')) %>% # remove duplicate current residence
  select(-seq(3,119,2)) %>% # remove MOE column
  select(-c('Same house 1 year ago', 'Population 1 year and over',
            'Same state of residence 1 year ago','Different state of residence 1 year ago'))

old_names = colnames(migrations[,2:ncol(migrations)])
new_names = as.character(unlist(migrations[1, 2:ncol(migrations)], use.names = FALSE))

migrations = migrations %>% rename_at(vars(old_names),~ new_names) %>% # change source column name
  drop_na() %>% filter(!target %in% c('United States2','Puerto Rico','Guam')) %>% 
  select(-c('Total', 'Puerto Rico', 'U.S. Island Area', 'Foreign Country')) %>% # remove aboard source and statistics
  gather(key='source', value='count' ,-target) # wide to long

migrations$count = migrations$count %>% as.numeric()
migrations = migrations[,c(2,1,3)]

task 4 ‘New York’, ‘Texas’, ‘Florida’, ‘Pennsylvania’

circlize

source_state=c('New York', 'Texas', 'Florida', 'Pennsylvania')
network = migrations %>% filter(source %in% source_state) %>% group_by(source) %>% top_n(10, wt=count)


chordDiagram(network, annotationTrack = c('grid'), 
    preAllocateTracks = list(track.height = max(strwidth(unlist(dimnames(network))))))

circos.track(track.index = 1, panel.fun = function(x, y) {
    circos.text(CELL_META$xcenter, CELL_META$ylim[1], CELL_META$sector.index, 
        facing = "clockwise", adj = c(0, 0.5),cex=0.8)}, bg.border = NA) 
title("Top 10 Migration Destinations of NY, TX, FL and PA", cex = 0.5)

igraph

network = migrations %>% filter(source %in% source_state) %>% group_by(source) %>% top_n(10, wt=count)
network=graph.data.frame(network)

plot(network,layout=layout_in_circle(network))
title('Top 10 Migration Destinations of NY, TX, FL and PA', cex = 0.5)
